OL,3,CConcerns raised over 'unfair'
OL,4,Capprenticeship funding model
OL,6,FWhereas, if you choose to start an
OL,7,Fapprenticeship, fees range from #700
OL,8,Fto #5,600 per year - with an average
OL,9,Ffee at Highlands costing #1,600 per
OL,10,Fyear.
OL,12,FCurrently, those studying
OL,13,Fapprenticeships at levels 2 and 3 have
OL,14,Faccess to a non-means-tested grant of
OL,15,F#1,852 per year.
OL,17,FBut those on Higher Apprenticeships,
OL,18,Fat levels 4 and above, can access
OL,19,Fmeans-tested grants for tuition up to
OL,20,F#9,535, as well as funds for living
OL,21,Fcosts up to #9,138.
